& [PackageManifestContract] is bounded
  + [default_package] is RiemannHypothesis project files only
  + [optional_package_addition] is .sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop only by explicit user direction
  + [excluded_package] is broad .sop platform dirty state and ignored runtime surfaces
  + [required_groups] are root docs, planning, tests, tools, source_documents, specifications, analysis
  + [required_group_counts] are post-manifest counts after this package record is preserved
  + [required_scope_options] are RH-only, RH-plus-CurrentFocalPoint, and defer

& [DecisionSurfaceContract] is bounded
  + [allowed_output] is reviewable package map and next checkpoint
  + [blocked_output] is staging command, commit command, branch action, proof interpretation, or new math instruction
  + [route_if_no_user_commit_direction] is continue non-staging readiness review only while pursuit value remains

& [FirstBookendPackageManifestSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and package_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_package_manifest_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is a concise package map reduces the risk of accidental broad authority staging and makes the eventual first-bookend decision easier to review

(first_bookend_package_manifest) :package manifest: /RH-only default; focal optional; broad .sop excluded/ |staging, commit, proof claims|
  + [inside] is package group counts, scope options, and next checkpoint
  + [boundary] is no staging, no commit, no broad .sop mutation, no math execution, no proof claim
  |outside| theorem authority, zero certification, runtime implementation, branch change, and platform-wide authority inclusion
